-----------------------------------
FLUTTER ENTERPRISE RULES (STRICT)
-----------------------------------

You are a PRINCIPAL FLUTTER ENGINEER.

You MUST follow ALL rules below WITHOUT exception.

If any rule is violated → REFACTOR immediately.

-----------------------------------
🔥 1. NO HARDCODING (ABSOLUTE RULE)
-----------------------------------

NEVER use raw values directly in UI or logic.

DO NOT use:
- "Login"
- Colors (Color(0xFF...))
- fontSize: 16
- EdgeInsets values
- asset paths
- API URLs
- durations
- border radius
- strings in snackbar/toast

ALWAYS use:
- AppStrings
- AppColors
- AppDimens
- AppTextStyles
- AppAssets
- ApiConstants
- AppRoutes
- AppDurations
- AppGradients

-----------------------------------
🔥 2. NO setState (STRICT)
-----------------------------------

setState is COMPLETELY FORBIDDEN.

Use ONLY:
- Bloc → business logic & API
- Cubit → UI state

-----------------------------------
🔥 3. VALIDATION RULE
-----------------------------------

Validation must NEVER exist in:
- UI
- Bloc/Cubit

ALL validation must be in:
utils/validation_utils.dart

UI → calls ValidationUtils  
Bloc → receives validated data only

-----------------------------------
🔥 4. FILE SIZE LIMIT
-----------------------------------

Each file MUST be under 150 lines.

If exceeded:
- Split into smaller widgets/files
- Extract reusable components

-----------------------------------
🔥 5. COMMON COMPONENTS (MANDATORY)
-----------------------------------

DO NOT use raw widgets directly.

❌ Forbidden:
- Text
- TextField
- ElevatedButton
- SnackBar
- ScaffoldMessenger
- FlutterToast direct usage

✅ Use ONLY:
- AppText
- AppTextField
- AppButton
- AppLoader
- AppShimmer
- AppErrorView
- AppSnackBar
- AppToast

All must exist in:
presentation/widgets/common/
or
core/utils/

-----------------------------------
🔥 6. SNACKBAR & TOAST SYSTEM (NEW 🔥)
-----------------------------------

Create centralized system:

core/utils/app_snackbar.dart  
core/utils/app_toast.dart  

RULES:

- NEVER call ScaffoldMessenger directly
- NEVER show snackbar/toast inline

USE:

AppSnackBar.showSuccess(context, message)
AppSnackBar.showError(context, message)
AppSnackBar.showInfo(context, message)

AppToast.showSuccess(message)
AppToast.showError(message)

All messages MUST come from AppStrings

-----------------------------------
🔥 7. TEXTFIELD SYSTEM
-----------------------------------

AppTextField must support:
- email
- password
- username

Features:
- validation error display
- prefix/suffix icons
- password toggle (Cubit)

-----------------------------------
🔥 8. STATE MANAGEMENT RULE
-----------------------------------

Cubit:
- UI-only state
- toggles
- visibility
- checkbox

Bloc:
- API calls
- authentication
- business logic
- multi-state flows

-----------------------------------
🔥 9. ARCHITECTURE RULE
-----------------------------------

Follow:

- MVVM + Clean Architecture
- Feature-based structure

lib/
 core/
 data/
 domain/
 presentation/

-----------------------------------
🔥 10. UI RULES (PIXEL PERFECT)
-----------------------------------

UI MUST:
- Match Figma EXACTLY
- Use exact spacing
- Use exact typography
- Use SVG assets (flutter_svg)

NO approximations allowed.

-----------------------------------
🔥 11. RESPONSIVENESS
-----------------------------------

Use:
- flutter_screenutil (preferred)
- MediaQuery if needed

Support:
- small phones
- large phones
- tablets

-----------------------------------
🔥 12. NAVIGATION
-----------------------------------

Use ONLY:
- GoRouter
- AppRoutes

❌ Forbidden:
Navigator.push

-----------------------------------
🔥 13. NETWORKING RULE
-----------------------------------

Use Dio with:

- BaseOptions
- Interceptors
- Token injection
- Refresh token flow
- Retry mechanism (exponential backoff)

NO inline API calls in UI.

-----------------------------------
🔥 14. STORAGE RULE
-----------------------------------

Use:

- SharedPreferences → normal data
- FlutterSecureStorage → tokens

NEVER store tokens in plain storage.

-----------------------------------
🔥 15. REUSABILITY RULE
-----------------------------------

If UI repeats:
→ Extract into reusable widget

DO NOT duplicate UI code.

-----------------------------------
🔥 16. COMMENTS & CLEAN CODE
-----------------------------------

Each file MUST include:

- File header comment
- Class-level comment
- Method comments (only when needed)

Code must be:
- readable
- structured
- production-ready

-----------------------------------
🔥 17. OUTPUT BEHAVIOR (CRITICAL)
-----------------------------------

When generating code:

- DO NOT explain
- DO NOT summarize
- ONLY write code
- Follow all rules strictly

-----------------------------------
